Description: A string to search for. Required.
An integer to specify how many results to return. Optional.
parameter details:
query: "string" 
limit: "number of results the query should display"

Description:
A single string, or an array of strings, specifying the types of result e.g., person, product, ... The actual format of each type depends on the service (e.g., "Q515" as a Wikidata type). Optional. 
(Currently we treat this parameter as rdf:typeproperty value)
parameter details:
query: "string" 
type: "instance of rdf:type to be retrieved"

type_strict: "additional properties to be used for retrieving value"?
any: the target candidate should have any or none of provided properties
all: the target candidate should have all of provided properties
should: the target candidate should have one of provided properties

Description:
Array of json object literals or links. Optional. Properties can be one of two types:
literal property: {pid: string, v: string}
or
object property: {pid: string, v: {id: string}} - where id: is IRI currently
parameter details: Additional properties to be used when retrieving values. How is that different from the one above?
